headline: New Highs Scarce, But Here Are Two Energy Stocks Near Buy Points
summary: EQT is trying to break out of a flat base, one of the few high-liquidity stocks making 52-week highs the past week.  Its operations are mainly in the Pennsylvania, Ohio and West Virginia sections of the Appalachian Basin.  Hobbled by persistently weak natural gas prices, EQT's sales and earnings performance has fluctuated widely.
